headline: Packaging firm International Paper to close four US plants, cut 1% of global jobs
summary: Memphis, Tennessee-headquartered International Paper has seen tepid demand for its pricey paper packaging as consumer goods companies temper inventories and opt for cheaper packaging options to lower costs.  International Paper, which bought UK rival DS Smith in a 5.8-billion-pound ($7.23 billion) deal in January, has been streamlining its operations in the United States as higher prices hit sales volumes.  Of its nearly 200 factories in the U.S., a containerboard mill in Louisiana, recycling plant in Arizona, box plant in Pennsylvania and sheet feeder plant in Missouri would cease operations by the end of April, International Paper said.
